1.	Unzip the file "open64_sdk1.0.tar.bz2"
2.	into a "Terminal" window, run the installation script "install.sh" as root user, using the comand "./install.sh"
3.	Follow the prompts to select and install the components
4.	Open the file "ReadMe.txt"
5.	It is neccesary to know the directory of installation of the open64, in this case was:
	/home/andres/amdsdk	
	Open a "Terminal"
	for $AMDSDK_ROOT write the next comand
	echo export PATH=$PATH:/home/andres/amdsdk/v1.0 >> ~/.bashrc
	for $DOCROOT write the next comand
	echo export PATH=$PATH:/home/andres/amdsdk/v1.0/pdf >> ~/.bashrc
	for $OPEN64_TC write the next comand
	echo export PATH=$PATH:/home/andres/amdsdk/v1.0/x86_open64-4.2.4/bin >> ~/.bashrc
	for $ACML write the next comands
	echo export PATH=$PATH:/home/andres/amdsdk/v1.0/acml/open64_64/lib >> ~/.bashrc
	echo export PATH=$PATH:/home/andres/amdsdk/v1.0/acml/open64_64/include >> ~/.bashrc
	echo export PATH=$PATH:/home/andres/amdsdk/v1.0/acml/open64_64_mp/lib >> ~/.bashrc
	echo export PATH=$PATH:/home/andres/amdsdk/v1.0/acml/open64_64_mp/include >> ~/.bashrc
	for $ACML_GPU write the next comands
	echo export PATH=$PATH:/home/andres/amdsdk/v1.0/acml_gpu/gfortran64/lib >> ~/.bashrc
	echo export PATH=$PATH:/home/andres/amdsdk/v1.0/acml_gpu/gfortran64/include >> ~/.bashrc
	for $AMD_LIBM write the next comands
	echo export PATH=$PATH:/home/andres/amdsdk/v1.0/amdlibm-2-1-lin64/lib/dynamic >> ~/.bashrc
	echo export PATH=$PATH:/home/andres/amdsdk/v1.0/amdlibm-2-1-lin64/lib/static >> ~/.bashrc
	echo export PATH=$PATH:/home/andres/amdsdk/v1.0/amdlibm-2-1-lin64/include >> ~/.bashrc
	Close Terminal
6.	on a new Terminal write
	echo $PATH | tr ":" "\n" | nl
	To show the contents of the PATH
7.	Unzip the file Codigo_UVLM.ZIP
8.	Go to the folder /Codigo_UVLM/Cвdigo colmenares/
	Unzip the file juaneco2710-guavlam-code-792357391fff (1).zip
9.	Go to the folder
	/Documents/GUAVLAM/Codigo_UVLM/Cвdigo colmenares/juaneco2710-guavlam-code-792357391fff/main
10.	Open the file Makefile
	It is neccesary to create the ACML variable, to do this it is neccesary to know the directory of installation of the open64, in this case was:
	/home/andres/amdsdk
	Then, after
	OBJS_DIR = obj/
	EXE_DIR = bin/
	write:
	ACML = /home/andres/amdsdk/v1.0/acml/open64_64
	Save the changes in Makefile and close it.
11.	On Terminal write
	make all
12.	If the error cannot find crti.o: No such file or directory
	appears then write:
	sudo find /usr/ -name crti*
	This command must give something like: /usr/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/crti.o
	Then write:
	LIBRARY_PATH=/usr/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu:$LIBRARY_PATH export LIBRARY_PATH
13.	On Terminal write
	make all
14. 	Thats All GUAVLAM is ready to use.
	
	



